## Our Mission

TechAI Explained exists to make complex technology accessible. We believe that AI agents, Kubernetes networking, and distributed systems shouldn't require a PhD to understand. Every tutorial we write aims to take a developer from "I've heard of this" to "I can build with this" in a single sitting.

## What We Cover

- **AI & LLMs** — agent architectures, prompt engineering, RAG, code generation, AI-powered developer tools
- **DevOps & Cloud** — Kubernetes, CI/CD, infrastructure-as-code, observability, platform engineering
- **Software Architecture** — event-driven design, microservices vs monoliths, real-time systems, API design
- **Developer Productivity** — tools, workflows, and practices that make engineering teams faster

## Content Principles

1. **Code over theory** — every tutorial includes working code examples you can copy and adapt
2. **Diagrams over paragraphs** — visual explanations for complex architectures
3. **Honest trade-offs** — we don't just tell you what to use; we tell you when NOT to use it
4. **Production-focused** — patterns that survive real traffic, not just demo-quality examples
5. **No prerequisites assumed** — each article is self-contained

## The Team

**TechAI Explained Team** is a group of engineers and educators passionate about developer education. We combine production experience across cloud platforms, distributed systems, and AI engineering with a focus on clear, practical communication.

Our content pipeline is partially automated — we use AI tools for research, drafting, and code generation, with human review for technical accuracy and editorial quality. We believe in practicing what we teach: if we write about AI code generation, we use it in our own workflow.

